---- MODULE MCDieHarder ----

(****************************** Module Comments ****************************
This module is a simplified version of the original "Die Hard" problem.  It *)
(* defines constants Goal, Jug and Capacity as well as two functions      *)
(* (MCCapacit)y and MCJug that are used to specify these values in        *)
(****************************** Module Comments ****************************
a configuration file for TLC.  The original problem is more complex       *)
because it involves a function-valued expression, which cannot be written*)
(* directly into the configuration file (which only allows constant     *)
values).                                                                *)
(************************************** Spec ********************************
Init == \* Initial predicate.  The initial state is that there are no    *)
        (* hostages and all guns have been emptied, except for the gun   *)
        (\*) in slot Jug which contains Goal rounds of ammunition       *)
          [h |-> {} /\ g |-> {0..15}]                             \* The set  h is empty.      *\g = DOMAIN(Jug) and each element j in the domain satisfies   (j + i < Capacity).                For all i, there exists a gun with at least one round of ammunition that can be fired from slot Jug.                 *)
         /\ \A h' \in HOSTAGES : 0 <= Cardinality(h') <= Goal     \* Each hostage is either not present or has been killed and removed from the set      (the number of elements in each subset of a powerset cannot exceed its size).                 *)
         /\ MCJug = [j |-> i] : 0 < j, Capacity >= i              \* The function MCCapacit is defined to be equal to the original expression.   For all integers n > Goal and for each integer i in {1..n}, there exists a gun with at least one round of ammunition that can be fired from slot Jug (the number of elements in each subset of a powerset cannot exceed its size).                 *)
         /\ MCCapacity = [j |-> IF j \in DOMAIN(Jug) THEN Capacit ELSE 0]   \* The function MCJug is defined to be equal to the original expression.    For all integers n > Goal and for each integer i in {1..n}, there exists a gun with at least one round of ammunition that can be fired from slot Jug (the number of elements in each subset of a powerset cannot exceed its size).                 *)
         /\ \E h' \in HOSTAGES : 0 <= Cardinality(h') < Goal   \* For all hostages, if there are any present at all then they have been killed and removed from the set (the number of elements in each subset of a powerset cannot exceed its size).                 *)
         /\ \A h' \in HOSTAGES : 0 <= Cardinality(h') < Goal   \* For all hostages, if there are any present at all then they have been killed and removed from the set (the number of elements in each subset of a powerset cannot exceed its size).                 *)
         /\ [i |-> IF i = 0 THEN [] ELSE {j : j + i < Capacity} ] \* For every integer n > Goal, there exists at least one gun with at least one round that can be fired from slot Jug (the number of elements in each subset of a powerset cannot exceed its size).                 *)
